5:
The heavens praise your wonders, Yahweh;
\q your truthfulness is praised in the assembly of the holy ones.
\q

9:
You rule the raging sea;
\q when the waves surge, you calm them.
\q

19:
Long ago you spoke in a vision to your faithful ones;
\q you said, "I have set a crown on a mighty one;
\q I have raised up one chosen from among the people.
\q

20:
I have chosen David my servant;
\q with my holy oil have I anointed him.
\q

21:
My hand will support him;
\q my arm will strengthen him.
\q

22:
No enemy will deceive him;
\q no son of wickedness will oppress him.
\q

24:
My truth and my covenant faithfulness will be with him;
\q by my name he will be victorious.
\q

28:
I will extend my covenant faithfulness to him forever;
\q and my covenant with him will be secure.
\q

38:
But you have refused and rejected;
\q you have been angry with your anointed king.
\q

42:
You have raised the right hand of his enemies;
\q you have made all his enemies rejoice.
\q

44:
You have brought his splendor to an end;
\q you have brought down his throne to the ground.
\q
